</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Taken" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Taken">Taken</a></em>: In "Charlie and Lisa", the title characters Charlie Keys and Lisa Clarke have sex in zero gravity aboard one of the alien ships.
</li><li> This came up on a particularly good game of <em>Press Conference</em> on the British version of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/WhoseLineIsItAnyway" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/WhoseLineIsItAnyway">Whose Line Is It Anyway?</a></em>, in which Tony Slattery had to guess who he was - <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aZBNyAFllyo">the first man to make love in space<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> - by the questions Stephen Frost, Colin Mochrie and Ryan Stiles asked him. In case you even needed to be told, there were <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleEntendre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleEntendre">double entendres</a> galore.
